  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2115",
  "title": "stats widget: Getting stats from DerivedHelper ",
  "body": "I have an InstantSearch with a `DerivedHelper`.\r\n\r\nI'm trying to get the results of the `DerivedHelper` from the Stats widget.\r\n\r\nHere's what I've tried (unsuccessfully):\r\n```js\r\nthis.InstantSearch.widgets.stats({\r\n  container: this.$container.find(this.config.selectors.stats)[0],\r\n  transformData: {\r\n    body: (data) => {\r\n      let helper = this.instantSearch.helper;\r\n      let locationsHelper = helper.derivedHelpers[0];\r\n\r\n      return Object.assign(data, {locationsHelper});\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  templates: {\r\n    body: (stats) => {\r\n      return stats.hasNoResults ? 'No trips found.' : `${stats.nbHits} ${pluralize('trip', stats.nbHits)} from ${pluralize('location', stats.locationsHelper.lastResults.nbHits)} locations`;\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}),\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt seems this happens too early, as `stats.locationsHelper` is always `null`. However, by the time I `console.log` it, I see my results. So it seems something is happening in the lifecycle of that helper that isn't propagated through the stats widget.\r\n\r\nIs there any way to do this, short of making my own custom stats widget?\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"algoliasearch-helper\": \"^2.18.1\",\r\n\"instantsearch.js\": \"^1.10.3\",\r\n```",
